Dana,<br>
     I beg your pardon.  There has been disagreement about how much racism there was, but I don't recall its existence being totally denied.  As for the term &quot;gooks&quot;; I've been told its origins are in the Korean War; and it wasn't any more complimentary then.  Too many used it, but quite a number of us, myself included, consider it offensive and have never used the term.
<p><code>-- gerald_ney@icpphil.navy.mil  (Gerald Ney, &quot;professor&quot;, 7/68-7/69) </code><p>


